==English==
===Etymology===
From late Latin ''[[#Latin|pericope]]'', from Greek ''[[περικοπή]]'' ‘section’, from ''[[peri-]]'' + ''[[κοπή]]'' ‘cutting’, from ''[[κόπτειν]]'' ‘to cut’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/pəˈrɪkəpi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A section of text, especially a passage of Scripture to be read in public worship.
#: ''The reader looked up the Sunday morning '''pericope'''.''
#: ''The oldest know system of '''pericopes''' in the Western Church is ascribed to Jerome.''

